Nigerian Fuji musician Obesere becomes a grandfather after his daughter put to bed. His daughter Susan and her husband today June 25, welcomed a newborn baby boy. The arrival of their newborn baby has now made Obesere a grandfather he has since longed to be. The “Egungun be careful” crooner shared the news on his verified Instagram page. He congratulated the couple and also prayed for the newborn baby boy. Obesere whose real name is Abass Akande wrote;“The news that you delivered of a bouncing baby boy woke me up this morning and has been making my day. READ ALSO I told God to kill me when I am 70 – Ajimobi Big congrats to my daughter, Susan and her husband. The new baby shall live to fulfil his purpose on Earth.”